Combine juice and 1/4 cup of the sugar in small saucepan. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until reduced to 1/3 cup. Cool to room temperature. Preheat broiler with rack about 4" from heat. Arrange grapefruit slices in single layer in large baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar. Broil 6 minutes or until grapefruit is flecked with brown. Arrange on serving platter or individual plates and drizzle with pomegranate syrup. For added crunch and flavor, sprinkle grapefruit slices with a few chopped pistachios and pomegranate seeds.